Six vehicles were extensively damaged on Saturday afternoon when a huge tree fell on them at the Serena Hotel in Nairobi. No injuries were reported.   Earlier, Kilimani OCPD Joseph Muthee said four top-of-the-range vehicles were at the car park when the tree fell on them. No one was in the cars at the time of the incident, he added.     Heavy rains in the country have left a wake of destruction.   In some areas, people and property have been swept away by floodwaters, while in others, houses have been submerged or flooded. The Meteorological Department warned of heavy rains this month. Additional reporting by Jeff Angote.   They were loading sand into a vehicle.